## 🔄 MIGRATION SQL (Détails)

Le fichier `supabase/migrations/20260211_create_public_user_trigger.sql` effectue :

### 1. Création de la fonction trigger
```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.handle_new_user()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  INSERT INTO public.users (id, email, email_verified, updated_at, created_at)
  VALUES (NEW.id, NEW.email, NEW.email_confirmed_at, NOW(), NOW())
  ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER;
```

### 2. Création du trigger
```sql
CREATE TRIGGER on_auth_user_created
  AFTER INSERT ON auth.users
  FOR EACH ROW
  EXECUTE FUNCTION public.handle_new_user();
```

### 3. Synchronisation des utilisateurs existants
```sql
INSERT INTO public.users (id, email, email_verified, updated_at, created_at)
SELECT id, email, email_confirmed_at, NOW(), created_at
FROM auth.users
WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT id FROM public.users)
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
```

